@DATABASE "Man"

@NODE MAIN "Man"

ViewAutoDOCS v1.1 - © 1993 by Markus Hillenbrand
------------------------------------------------

ViewAutoDOCS is a program to handle autodoc-files, the documentations
of the amiga libraries.

@{" Requirements " Link Requirements}
@{" The Convert Program " Link The_Convert_Program}
@{" Description " Link Description}
@{" Localisation under WB2.1+ " Link Localisation_under_WB2.1+}
@{" Tooltypes " Link Tooltypes}
@{" Copyright " Link Copyright}
@{" Future Plans " Link Future_Plans}
@{" Address of the author " Link Address_of_the_author}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements "Requirements"

You need:            - asl.library         v37
                     - intuition.library   v37
                     - gadtools.library    v37
                     - graphics.library    v37
                     - dos.library         v37
		     - icon.library        v37 
		     - commodities.library v37
                     - autodocs to convert

Supported:           - locale.library      v38
                     - reqtools.library    v38

Recommended:         - a harddisk to use the program efficiently
                     - processor >MC18010, because of font-sensitivity


@ENDNODE

@NODE The_Convert_Program "The Convert Program"

The program Convert converts an autodoc-file into hady file wich can
easily be loaded by ViewAutoDOCS. You MUST have a directory called 
VAD: to use any of the programs.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Description "Description"

ViewAutoDOCS is a commodity, therefore it stays in memory until you
end the program. You can call it through a hotkey. You can alse use
Exchange to handle the program.

The program´s window offers the following features:

@{" Select Library " Link Select_Library}
@{" Select Function " Link Select_Function}
@{" Hide " Link Hide}
@{" Quit " Link Quit}
@{" Screenmode (menu) " Link Screenmode_(menu)}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Select_Library "Select Library"

Here you can select a library stored in VAD:. A requester will open
which can be handled by mouse or keys. The first function of the 
selected library will be opened an shown in the listview-gadget.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Select_Function "Select Function"

Here you can select a function of the selected library. It will be
shown in the listview.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Hide "Hide"

The program´s window will be closed until you press the program´s
hotkey again.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Quit "Quit"

The program will end and will be put out of memory.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Screenmode_(menu) "Screenmode (menu)"

If you have not selected the window-mode, you can can change the
screenmode here (>OS 2.1)


@ENDNODE

@NODE Localisation_under_WB2.1+ "Localisation under WB2.1+"

Since Workbench 2.1 the program can be localized, i.e. it can be translated
into several languages. Therefor I added the C source of the catalog. In the
original only the german and english version are supported.
The C source kann easily be changed, and with a suitable program (i.e. 
MakeCat - © Paladin-Software etc.) you can rebuild the catalog.
If you have created a new catalog it would be nice if you send me the new
C source via e-mail. Perhaps I can add the new language in a newer version
of man.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Tooltypes "Tooltypes"

If you want to configure the program on your own, you must change the tool-
types in 'ViewAutoDOCS.info'. The following tooltypes are supported:

@{" DONOTWAIT " Link DONOTWAIT}
@{" CX_PRIORITY " Link CX_PRIORITY}
@{" CX_POPKEY  " Link CX_POPKEY_}
@{" FONTNAME " Link FONTNAME}
@{" FONTSIZE " Link FONTSIZE}
@{" LISTVIEWFONTNAME " Link LISTVIEWFONTNAME}
@{" LISTVIEWFONTSIZE " Link LISTVIEWFONTSIZE}
@{" PUBSCREEN " Link PUBSCREEN}
@{" WINDOWXSIZE " Link WINDOWXSIZE}
@{" WINDOWYSIZE " Link WINDOWYSIZE}
@ENDNODE

@NODE DONOTWAIT "DONOTWAIT"

This tooltype is not important. It is only used by your Amiga when you boot
your system and when the program lies in SYS:WBStartup.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CX_PRIORITY "CX_PRIORITY"

This tooltype changes the commodity´s priority, the default value is 0.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CX_POPKEY_ "CX_POPKEY "

This tooltype says which hotkey will activate the program and open the
window. Here you can enter all values allowed by the style-guide from CBM.
The default value is CTRL LALT DEL.

@ENDNODE

@NODE FONTNAME "FONTNAME"

Here you enter the name of the font which will be used in the gadgets.
This font should NOT be proportional. Even scalable fonts do not always
fit in the gadgets. Therefore you should use a fixed bitmap font. Or you
try some of your fonts.

If the tooltype is enclosed in brackets (FONTNAME=...), the default prefs
font will be chosen.

If you use this tooltype, you also have to use FONTSIZE.

@ENDNODE

@NODE FONTSIZE "FONTSIZE"

Here you can enter the size for the font in FONTNAME. If you do not enter
a value, the font from your prefs will be chosen.

If you use this tooltype, you also have to use FONTNAME.

@ENDNODE

@NODE LISTVIEWFONTNAME "LISTVIEWFONTNAME"

Here you can enter the name of the font which will be used in the main
listview gadget. This font can be proportional and/or scalable. 

@ENDNODE

@NODE LISTVIEWFONTSIZE "LISTVIEWFONTSIZE"

Here you can enter the size for the font in LISTVIEWFONTSIZE. If you do not 
enter a value, the font from your prefs will be chosen.

@ENDNODE

@NODE PUBSCREEN "PUBSCREEN"

Here you can enter a pubscreen name to open the program´s window upon.
If you do not enter a name, the program will open its own screen.

@ENDNODE

@NODE WINDOWXSIZE "WINDOWXSIZE"

If the window opens on a pubscreen, the window will have this width;
if the value is 0, the window´s width will be a minimum. Wrong values
will be changed automatically.

@ENDNODE

@NODE WINDOWYSIZE "WINDOWYSIZE"

Same as WINDOWXSIZE, but for the height of the window.


@ENDNODE

